title: Wrestling: South Feature Athlete - Thomas Jefferson's Dustin Lanning
text:
Home Thomas Jefferson Wrestling: South Feature Athlete - Thomas Jefferson's Dustin Lanning Wrestling: South Feature Athlete - Thomas Jefferson's Dustin Lanning Written by Ken Wunderley on Wednesday, 22 February 2017 10:59 am . 
Sport: Wrestling Weight Class: 220 
Background Info: Lanning is a three-year starter at 220 pounds. He broke into Thomas Jefferson's starting lineup as a sophomore and placed fifth in Class AAA Section 2. He finished that season with a 16-16 record after an appearance in the WPIAL Tournament. Last season, he placed fourth in the section and made a second WPIAL appearance. He finished with a 21-15 record. This season, he enters this weekend's section tournament with a 22-5 record. He placed fourth in the Eastern Area Invitational and fourth in the Allegheny County Tournament. Lanning was also a tackle for the Jaguars football team, which won WPIAL titles in 2015 and 2016. 
Thomas Jefferson School District: Home of the Jaguars. South Teams
